<div class="postright">
<h3>USB Encrypted Persistence</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Hi All,</p><p>Just wondering how to setup an USB LUKS encrypted Persistence on the Parrot OS. Being following the guide on how to setup it up on the Kali distro which has worked fine in the past...see this link:&#160; http://docs.kali.org/downloading/kali-linux-live-usb-persistence.</p><p>I seem to run into a brickwall on this command &#039;sudo echo &quot;/ union&quot; &gt; /mnt/my_usb/persistence.conf&#039; as I get the error &quot;Permission Denied&quot;</p><p>Any thoughts or solutions?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="inbox">
<div class="postfoot clearb">
<div class="postfootleft"><p><span>Offline</span></p></div>
</div>
